The paper proposes a framework for few-shot learning using deep meta-learning, which involves learning a representation for each instance that captures its high-level concept. This involves the integration of deep learning into meta-learning, which is a popular topic in the machine learning community. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with natural language processing tasks, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the use of neural networks for learning to learn suggests that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
